I"d<p>The <code>coinmarketcap</code> sensor platform displays various details about a cryptocurrency provided by <a href="https://coinmarketcap.com/">CoinMarketCap</a>.</p>
<p>To add the CoinMarketCap sensor to your installation, add the following lines to your <code>configuration.yaml</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
sensor:
  - platform: coinmarketcap
</code></pre>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='currency_id' href='#currency_id'></a> currency_id</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='integer'>integer</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>The ID of the cryptocurrency to use, default is the ID of Bitcoin.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>1</p>
</p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='display_currency' href='#display_currency'></a> display_currency</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>The currency to display.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>USD</p>
</p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='display_currency_decimals' href='#display_currency_decimals'></a> display_currency_decimals</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='integer'>integer</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>The amount of decimals to round to.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>2</p>
</p></dd></dl>
</div>
<p>All supported currencies can be found <a href="https://coinmarketcap.com/api/">here</a>, a list of currency IDs can be found <a href="https://api.coinmarketcap.com/v2/ticker/">here</a>.</p>
